7:
I get it! Heat in the kitchen can feel
like rounding the corner to the final
stretch of a race!
11:
But that's just it! You're in the final
stretch—You can't turn back now!
Push yourself and go where no
yakisoba chef has gone before!
14:
Hnngh... You're right, Golshi! I'll show
them who's boss!
25:
Heya, perfect timing! Wanna try
some Golshi-approved deluxe
yakisoba?
28:
On sale now for zero percent off!
Wow, what a deal, Mary!
It sure is, Bob!
32:
Uhhh... Mind explaining what's going
on?
38:
So you taught some brat how to
make yakisoba, and then he ran his
little mouth at the neighborhood
restaurants.
42:
Hey, hey, don't make this sound like
some dumb feud.
45:
This is a battle for the ages!
Yakisoba versus pasta versus
ramen versus whatever other
noodles wanna join in!
52:
Brought to you by our beloved
sponsors: the Guild, the Lord of the
Uma Golshi, and our wonderful local
vendors.
56:
Sounds like you wanna suck us into
a stupid fight.
59:
Hey Alk, speaking of food, why don't
we get outta here and—
64:
This DOES have potential... Sure, it's
yakisoba, but what's this flavor?
Does it come from the grill?
68: Come on, even for you, this is fast.
73:
Oho... Sounds like you know your
saucy noodles.
77:
Oh, I don't know about that... By the
way, what do you think your
chances are?
81:
We're talking about
Golshi-approved deluxe yakisoba
here! The gold is ours for the taking!
83:
Or that's what I want to say. But
there are no guarantees in war. I'm
sure that's what's got this kid scared.
86:
Well, yeah... We're up against chefs
with the Guild's seal of approval!
87:
Sure, all our prices are gonna be the
same for this competition, but
they've got access to way better
ingredients!
91:
Like I said, kid, this and that are
totally different things.
94:
Of course pasta's gonna be fancy.
That's where its aptitude lies!
Yakisoba's strength lies in its identity
as a festival food—a treat for the
common man!
98:
In other words, we don't have to
compete in the same way they are.
101:
The Noodle Cup event is a FESTIVAL.
There's no better place to showcase
yakisoba's potential!
105:
We're looking at a reversal of
culinary norms. People don't want
fine dining at a festival—they want a
party in their mouths!
109:
Atta boy, Alk! I knew you'd get it!
Getting a little beach sand in your
teeth is all a part of the yakisoba
experience!
117:
You got something against seaside
yakisoba stalls? How dare you say
that in front of Gold Ship, President
of the Space Beach Business Bureau!
130:
I'd understand ramen or even that
pasta place...
133:
But who ever heard of soba, udon,
AND somen outpacing yakisoba?!
136:
Yeah, I thought we'd leave them in
the dust... What happened?
139:
This is bad! At this rate, we're going
to have... leftovers!
143:
Leftovers?! Of MY yakisoba?! Does
this spell... defeat?
147:
No, snap out of it, me! My dream of
world domination can't end here!
152:
This isn't the time for your jokes! At
this rate, the kid's stand is going to
go under!
156:
Calm yourself, Alk. The shrimp has
what it takes—he just needs
something to reel the customers in.
161:
Speaking of which, I'm off to snag
me some shrimp!
173:
Wait, that's it! Nimbus, go buy us
some extra ingredients!
177:
Huh? C'mon, you can't take that
nutjob seriously!
181:
But she's right! The problem is our
menu! People like normal yakisoba
just fine, but they're not gonna buy
more than one serving.
184:
Unless it's SEAFOOD yakisoba. That's
the answer.
189: Why... Why didn't you just give up?
191:
I saw Golshi running at the
academy, you know.
192:
She may have lagged behind in the
beginning, but she just kept
running—faster and faster—until she
was neck and neck with the others.
194:
And you used the same strategy...
Guess I played right into your hands.
197:
Greetings! The great Golshi has
returned! I've brought you all some
delicious sea snails.
203: Golshi! We won! Your yakisoba did it!
206:
Whoa, seriously? I knew my
yakisoba was the real deal!
209:
Your pasta was pretty good too, you
know. Probably the hundredth most
delicious in the galaxy.
212:
Is that, uh... supposed to be a
compliment?
215:
Considering your skills, how about
we all become pals? My little buddy
put up a good fight, didn't he?
219:
Wait... Wasn't the brat the one who
started this mess?
